  "prompt": "What should I do if someone loves me a lot more than I love him?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful steps to consider:\n\n1. Be honest with yourself\n- Assess your true feelings\n- Don't try to force emotions you don't have\n- Understand the difference between affection and love\n\n2. Communicate openly and kindly\n- Be direct about your feelings\n- Explain your emotional state clearly\n- Avoid giving false hope\n- Be respectful of their feelings\n\n3. Consider the relationship's potential\n- Evaluate if there's compatibility\n- Think about whether feelings might grow\n- Decide if you want to invest more time and emotional energy\n\n4. Set clear boundaries\n- Be clear about your emotional availability\n- Don't lead them on\n- Respect their feelings while protecting yours\n\n5. Give space if needed\n- Sometimes distance helps emotional readiness\n- Allow both parties to process feelings\n\n6. Be compassionate\n- Recognize their vulnerability\n- Treat their emotions with respect\n- Avoid being cruel or dismissive\n\n7. Make a decision\n- Choose to either:\n- Work on deepening your connection\n- End the relationship kindly\n- Maintain friendship if possible\n\nRemember: It's okay to not have the same intense feelings. Honesty and kindness are most important.\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific situation in more detail?",
